Player Killing on Darkwind (or PK'ing).
 
     This has to do with players killing other players here on the mud.
It is allowed, but only among those that register for it.  Be warned
though that registering for PK is a one way street.  Once you register
for it you are stuck with it for the rest of your life.  If you are
killed repetedly and constantly for no other reason than you happen
to be registered, then so be it, you will have to live with the
consequences of your decision.  Registering is not a decision to be
taken lightly, so make sure you think it though thouroughly.
 
What does registering do for you you might ask? First, it allows you
to basically kill anyone else who is also registered as a PK'er.  If
someone wrongs you, you can kill them for it plain and simple (or at
least attempt to).  It also means that ANY other registered player
can kill you any time the mood hits them, they don't need a reason
other than they felt like it, even if they kill you 20 times in a row,
or every time you log on for that matter.  If you find yourself in a
bad situation, dont come complaining to the admin, becasue you chose
your fate.  You need to try and find friends and alliances to help
you out of your situation, or start over.
